  <h3>
    Best Sunscreens
  </h3>

  <p>

    Sunscreen is one of the most important skin care
    products for protecting the skin from sun damage,
    dark spots, premature aging, and harmful UV rays.

  </p>

  <br>

  <p>

    Dermatologists recommend using a broad-spectrum
    sunscreen with SPF 30 or higher every day
    to protect the skin from both UVA and UVB rays.

  </p>

  <br>

  <p>

    For oily skin, lightweight gel or water-based
    sunscreens are usually the best choice because
    they absorb quickly without leaving a greasy finish.

  </p>

  <br>

  <p>

    Dry skin types should look for moisturizing
    sunscreens that contain hydrating ingredients
    like hyaluronic acid, ceramides, and glycerin.

  </p>

  <br>

  <p>

    Sensitive skin may benefit from mineral sunscreens
    that contain zinc oxide or titanium dioxide,
    because they are generally gentler on the skin.

  </p>

  <br>

  <p>

    Some of the best sunscreen ingredients include:

  </p>

  <br>

  <ul style="padding-left:20px; color:#555;">

    <li>
      <strong>Zinc Oxide</strong> – provides strong broad-spectrum protection and is suitable for sensitive skin.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      <strong>Titanium Dioxide</strong> – helps block harmful UV rays and works well for delicate skin.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      <strong>Hyaluronic Acid</strong> – keeps the skin hydrated and prevents dryness.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      <strong>Niacinamide</strong> – helps reduce redness, controls oil, and improves skin texture.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      <strong>Ceramides</strong> – strengthen the skin barrier and lock in moisture.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      <strong>Vitamin E</strong> – provides antioxidant protection against environmental damage.
    </li>

  </ul>

  <br>

  <p>

    Ingredients some people may prefer to avoid include:

  </p>

  <br>

  <ul style="padding-left:20px; color:#555;">

    <li>
      Heavy fragrances that may irritate sensitive skin.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      High amounts of alcohol that can dry out the skin.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      Oxybenzone, which may cause irritation for some skin types.
    </li>

    <br>

    <li>
      Thick oily ingredients that can clog pores and trigger acne.
    </li>

  </ul>

  <br>

  <p>

    Reapplying sunscreen every 2 hours is important,
    especially after sweating or swimming,
    to maintain effective sun protection throughout the day.

  </p>

